The paper deals with the problem of sensor data fusion for autonomous mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The fusion is between LiDAR and camera data, which are both commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a Gaussian Process regression-based algorithm, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and the algorithm is used for resolution matching, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses the problem of perception, which is a key aspect of autonomous systems (cs.SY).
